{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#5081: Throw an error on createVNode with using `innerHTML` and `children` at the same time",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:26:56.149054+00:00",
  "text": "Throw an error on createVNode with using `innerHTML` and `children` at the same time\n\n### Version\r\n3.2.24\r\n\r\n### Reproduction link\r\n[codesandbox.io](https://codesandbox.io/s/brave-lamport-r6fi4?file=/src/main.js)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n```\r\nimport { createApp, defineComponent, h } from \"vue\";\r\n\r\nconst App = defineComponent({\r\n  setup() {\r\n    return () => h(\"div\", { innerHTML: undefined }, \"a\");\r\n  }\r\n});\r\n\r\ncreateApp(App).mount(\"#app\");\r\n```\r\n\r\nI want to change innerHTML of props and children dynamic at same time.\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\n\r\nno Error and use innerHTML if provided or children content.\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\n\r\nthrow an error.\r\n\r\n`TypeError Cannot read properties of undefined (reading '__asyncLoader')`\r\n\r\n<!-- generated by vue-issues. DO NOT REMOVE -->",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":cake: p2-nice-to-have"
  ],
